All Classes

  • All Classes Interface Summary Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ApiEpisodeLoader
    ApiEpisodeLoader is responsible for calling the API and returning the full API response for a single episode based on that episode's API id
    Auth
    Manages Amazon Web Service authorization tokens and credentials management for log in endpoint calls
    BuildUserOwnList
    BuildUserOwnList provides functionality for the construction of a registered user's list of owned seasons and their associated episodes
    CognitoJWTParser
    Utility class for all operations on JWT.
    CognitoTokenHeader  
    Database  
    DatabaseSnapshot
    DatabaseSnapshot is responsible for generating ArrayLists representing current values of the database at the time the class is called.
    Episode
    Episode entity class
    EpisodeSelect
    EpisodeSelect controls the classes related to constructing an episode ID pool, random number pool, and applying the processing logic to select a random episode and return it for display in the JSP
    FetchEpisodeId
    Retrieves the API episode id from an ArrayList of Episode entities using the randomly generated number at index 0 of the passed Integer ArrayList
    FetchUser
    Process AWS authentication token data to determine the existence of user credentials in the database, and persist them if the user is new or retrieve them if user already exists.
    Keys  
    KeysItem  
    LogIn
    Manages Amazon Web Service log out endpoint calls
    LogOut
    Manages Amazon Web Service log out endpoint calls
    ModifyOwnership
    ModifyOwnership provides the direct DAO functionality to perform persistence operations with Own entities and their related entity objects
    Own
    Own entity class
    OwnershipManager
    OwnershipManager handles operations that involve adding and updating Own entities and their persistence state
    PropertiesLoader
    This interface contains a default method that can be used anywhere a Properties object is needed to be loaded.
    Season
    Season entity class
    SeasonComparator
    The SeasonComparator is a custom comparator class for use in sorting ArrayList objects via lambda methods.
    SessionFactoryProvider
    This file provides a SessionFactory for use with DAOs using Hibernate
    Startup
    Startup loads a Properties file at servlet startup
    Status
    Status entity class
    TokenResponse  
    TrekDao<T>
    TrekDao provides a universal set of methods for accessing and modifying persistence objects via Hibernate.
    UpdateDatabaseManager
    UpdateDatabaseManager controls the functionality of the UpdateSeasonList and UpdateEpisodeList classes
    UpdateEpisodeList
    UpdateEpisodeList is responsible for handling API calls to the STAPI source, retrieving all Episode entities there, and comparing the retrieved list against the existing database to identify new content for addition to the database.
    UpdateSeasonList
    UpdateSeasonList is responsible for handling API calls to the STAPI source, retrieving all Season entities there, and comparing the retrieved list against the existing database to identify new content for addition to the database.
    User
    User entity class
    UserLoader
    UserLoader queries the database and loads User data for authenticated users into the HTTP session
    View
    View entity class
    ViewManager
    ViewManager handles operations that involve adding and updating View entities and their persistence state
